---

## 1. Main Container

This is the top-level `div` that wraps and centers the form on the page.

* **Main Element:** `<div>`
* **Key Class:** `main-container`

---

## 2. Form Container

This is the central card that holds the heading, form, and back link.

* **Main Element:** `<div>`
* **Key Class:** `form-container`
* **Sub-components:**
    * `<h2>`: The main heading "Forgot Password".
    * `<p>`: Instructional text ("Enter your email...").
    * `<form>`: The main form element.
        * **ID:** `forgotPasswordForm` (This is the **key selector** your JavaScript will use).
        * Contains one `div.input-group` holding the email `<input>`.
        * Contains a `<button type="submit">` to submit the form.
    * `<p class="text-center">`: A wrapper for the "Back to Login" link.
        * `<a>`: A link pointing back to the login page.

---

## 3. Assets & Scripts

These are the files loaded at the end of the `<body>` to add functionality.

* **CSS:**
    * `/css/forgotPassword.css`: The custom stylesheet for this page.
* **JavaScript:**
    * `axios.min.js`: The Axios library, used to send the user's email to your server.
    * `/js/config.js`: (Likely contains your `BASE_URL`).
    * `/js/forgot-password.js`: The script that will listen for the `forgotPasswordForm` submission, send the email via Axios, and show a success/error message.